import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.scatterplot(x="US_Gross", y="Worldwide_Gross", data=data)
    ax.axhline(data['Worldwide_Gross'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Worldwide_Gross Median')
    ax.axvline(data['US_Gross'].median(), color='green', linestyle='--', label='US_Gross Median')
    plt.legend(loc='upper left')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of US_Gross and Worldwide_Gross?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='Production_Budget', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['Production_Budget'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median Budget: {:.2f}'.format(data['Production_Budget'].median()))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Production_Budget?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    plt.xlabel('Production Budget')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax = sns.boxplot(data=data[['Rotten_Tomatoes_Rating', 'IMDB_Rating']], palette="Set3")
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of Rotten_Tomatoes_Rating and IMDB_Rating?', wrap=True)
    ax.set_xlabel('Rating Type')
    ax.set_ylabel('Rating')
    ax.axhline(y=data['Rotten_Tomatoes_Rating'].median(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Rotten Tomatoes Median')
    ax.axhline(y=data['IMDB_Rating'].median(), color='b', linestyle='--', label='IMDB Median')
    ax.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.show()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='Running_Time_min', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['Running_Time_min'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['Running_Time_min'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['Running_Time_min'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['Running_Time_min'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Running_Time_min?')
    plt.xlabel('Running Time (min)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    chart = sns.countplot(x="MPAA_Rating", data=data, palette="Set2")
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, horizontalalignment='right')
    chart.axhline(y=data['MPAA_Rating'].value_counts().max(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Max Count: {:.2f}'.format(data['MPAA_Rating'].value_counts().max()))
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of MPAA_Rating?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
